{"id": "1422517989214785569", "channel_id": "1422517989214785569", "type": 0, "author_id": "478214049033879563", "author_name": "yannic2112", "author_bot": false, "content": "When I play Mice Assembly without the leap effect and then use some sort of card drawing ability (be that Annihilation, the card draw orision or the card itself says that I draw a card), the card that I draw is in 99% of the time Swarm Impact. This also works when I end the turn, the cards drawn for the next turn almost always include Swarm Impact. \nThis bug works regardless of how large my Draw Pile is. So it seems that for some reason, even when you play Mice Assembly without the leap effect, that the leap effect still takes place.", "timestamp": "2025-09-30T09:38:37.735000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1422517989214785569", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "[Bug] Jenkin‘ Mice Assembly uses leap effect too often", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1361168893200044183"]}
